        <h2>Transitioning Litter</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="guide-content">
        <p>
          Cats can be particular. Don't switch all at once. The gradual
          approach works best. <a href="{{ site.purrify.faq | utm('guide-transition') }}">Read our transition FAQs</a>.
        </p>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li><strong>Week 1:</strong> Mix 25% new litter with 75% old</li>
          <li><strong>Week 2:</strong> Move to 50/50 mix</li>
          <li><strong>Week 3:</strong> Increase to 75% new</li>
          <li><strong>Week 4:</strong> Complete the switch</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If your cat shows avoidance at any stage, slow down. Some cats
          need longer to adjust. That's normal. 
          <a href="{{ site.purrify.contact | utm('guide-transition') }}">Contact us for personalized help</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          For step-by-step transition support, compare recommendations from the
          <a href="https://www.vet.cornell.edu/departments-centers-and-institutes/cornell-feline-health-center" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> Cornell Feline Health Center</a>
